I"w4<p>A few users have asked me how I’ve created the Subscribe box in the sidebar and some have even called for a WordPress plugin that helps automate it.  In reality, it’s just simple HTML/CSS paired with the <a href="http://feedburner.google.com/fb/a/emailsyndication">Feedburner subscribe code</a> and can be replicated very easily.  Let’s take a look at the code used to create it:</p>

<div class="download">
  <a href="http://devgrow.s3.amazonaws.com/assets/files/subscribe.zip" class="button primary">Download at Github</a>
  <a href="http://demos.devgrow.com/subscribe/" class="button secondary">View Example</a>
</div>

<p><a href="http://demos.devgrow.com/subscribe/"><img src="http://devgrow.s3.amazonaws.com/assets/images/subscribe-big.gif" alt="" /></a></p>

<h3 id="the-html">The HTML</h3>

